entry.title: The Political Parties and Elections Act 2009 (Commencement No. 5 and Saving Provisions) Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order brings into force several provisions in the Political Parties and Elections Act 2009 (c. 12), and makes saving provisions in relation to some of those provisions.

entry.title: The Political Parties, Elections and Referendums (Civil Sanctions) Order 2010

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Political Parties, Elections and Referendums (Civil Sanctions) Order 2010

entry.summary: This Order is made under Schedule 19C to the Political Parties, Elections and Referendums Act 2000. It permits the Electoral Commission to impose civil sanctions in relation to the offences and the restrictions and requirements prescribed in Schedule 2 to the Order.

entry.title: The Disabled People’s Right to Control (Pilot Scheme) (England) Regulations 2010

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Disabled People’s Right to Control (Pilot Scheme) (England) Regulations 2010

entry.summary: Section 41 of the Welfare Reform Act 2009 enables the Secretary of State by regulations to make provision for the purpose of enabling disabled people aged 18 or over to exercise greater choice in relation to, and greater control over, the way in which certain services are provided to or for them by or on behalf of public bodies. Section 44 enables regulations under section 41 to make temporary provision as a pilot scheme.

title.div: The Local Health Boards (Consultation with Local Dental Committees) (Wales) Regulations 2010 / Rheoliadau Byrddau Iechyd Lleol (Ymgynghori â Phwyllgorau Deintyddol Lleol) (Cymru) 2010

div.p: These Regulations provide that a Local Health Board, in the exercise of its functions relating to primary dental services, must consult any committee recognised by it under section 69 of the NHS (Wales) Act 2006 (c. 42) on such occasions and to such extent as prescribed.

Mae'r Rheoliadau hyn yn darparu bod rhaid i Fwrdd Iechyd Lleol, wrth iddo arfer ei swyddogaethau sy'n ymwneud â gwasanaethau deintyddol sylfaenol, ymgynghori ag unrhyw bwyllgor a gydnabyddir ganddo o dan adran 69 o Ddeddf y GIG (Cymru) 2006 (p.42) ar yr adegau ac i'r graddau a ragnodir.

entry.title: The Regulation of Investigatory Powers (Scotland) Amendment Order 2010

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Regulation of Investigatory Powers (Scotland) Amendment Order 2010

entry.summary: This Order amends the Regulation of Investigatory Powers (Scotland) Act 2000 (asp11) to add the Common Services Agency for the Scottish Health Service as a relevant public authority which may grant authorisations for the use of directed surveillance and covert human intelligence sources.

entry.title: The Plant Health (Import Inspection Fees) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2010
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Plant Health (Import Inspection Fees) (Northern Ireland) Regulations 2005 (S.R. 2005/373) (“the principal Regulations”). The principal Regulations implement Article 13d of Council Directive 2000/29/EC (O.J. No. L 169, 10.7.2000, p1) (“the Directive”) which requires Member States to charge fees to cover the costs of documentary, identity and plant health checks of certain imports of plants, plant products and other objects from third countries.

entry.title: The Legal Services Act 2007 (Commencement No. 9) Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order is the ninth commencement order made under the Legal Services Act 2007 (c. 29) (“the 2007 Act”).

entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Tax Avoidance Schemes (Prescribed Descriptions of Arrangements) Regulations 2006 (S.I. 2006/1543 amended by S.I. 2007/2484 and S.I. 2009/2033) (“the principal regulations”).

entry.title: The Veterinary Surgeons and Veterinary Practitioners (Registration) Regulations Order of Council 2010
entry.summary: This Order approves the Veterinary Surgeons and Veterinary Practitioners (Registration) Regulations 2010 (“the Regulations”) made by the Council of the Royal College of Veterinary Surgeons (“the RCVS”) under section 11 of the Veterinary Surgeons Act 1966 (“the Act”). The new Regulations revoke the Veterinary Surgeons and Veterinary Practitioners (Registration) Regulations 2005, the Veterinary Surgeons and Veterinary Practitioners (Registration) (Amendment) Regulations 2007 and the Veterinary Surgeons and Veterinary Practitioners (Registration) (Amendment) Regulations 2008 and replace them with the Regulations set out in the Schedule. This Order revokes the Veterinary Surgeons and Veterinary Practitioners (Registration) Regulations Order of Council 2005, the Veterinary Surgeons and Veterinary Practitioners (Registration) (Amendment) Regulations Order of Council 2007 and the Veterinary Surgeons and Veterinary Practitioners (Registration) (Amendment) Regulations Order of Council 2008. It comes into force on 31st March 2011.

entry.title: The Community Health Partnerships (Scotland) Amendment Regulations 2010
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Community Health Partnerships (Scotland) Regulations 2004 (“the principal Regulations”).

entry.title: The Producer Responsibility Obligations (Packaging Waste) (Amendment) Regulations 2010

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Producer Responsibility Obligations (Packaging Waste) (Amendment) Regulations 2010

entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Producer Responsibility Obligations (Packaging Waste) Regulations 2007 (S.I. 2007/871) (the “2007 Regulations”), which implement Article 6(1) of Council Directive 94/62/EC on packaging and packaging waste (OJ No L 365, 31.12.1994, p 10) as amended by Directive 2004/12/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council (OJ No L 47, 18.2.2004, p 26).

entry.title: The Education (Student Support) (No. 2) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2009 (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2010
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Education (Student Support) (No. 2) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2009 (“the 2009 Regulations”). The 2009 Regulations provide for financial support for students taking designated higher education courses in respect of an academic year beginning on or after 1st September 2010.

entry.title: The Sheep Scab (Scotland) Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order replaces the Sheep Scab Order 1997 in so far as it extends to Scotland. This Order does not apply in the local government area of the Shetland Islands. The Shetland Islands Council are empowered to make regulations concerning sheep scab by the Sheep Scab (Shetland Islands) Order 2003.

entry.title: The Rent Officers (Housing Benefit Functions) Amendment Order 2010
entry.summary: This Order amends the Rent Officers (Housing Benefit Functions) Order 1997 (“the Rent Officers Order”) and the Rent Officers (Housing Benefit Functions) (Scotland) Order 1997.

entry.title: The Sexual Offences (Scotland) Act 2009 (Supplemental and Consequential Provisions) Order 2010

ukm:Supersedes.dc:title: The Sexual Offences (Scotland) Act 2009 (Supplemental and Consequential Provisions) Order 2010

entry.summary: This Order makes amendments to primary and secondary legislation relating to sexual offences. The amendments are supplemental and consequential to the Sexual Offences (Scotland) Act 2009 (“the 2009 Act”).
